<subSubSection id="74AE650BFFB8F706FF42256542C97C94" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="288" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" type="description">
<paragraph id="3C0B3680FFB8F705FF42256544B77E49" blockId="8.[151,1437,834,2013]" box="[151,1155,834,859]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="0EC0EA92FFB8F705FF422565411D7E48" bold="true" box="[151,297,834,859]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">Description.</emphasis>
Body length (from apex of vertex to tip of forewings): male 8.8 mm (n = 
<number id="8A7C24A7FFB8F705FBB1256544457E49" box="[1124,1137,834,858]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="1.0">1</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3C0B3680FFB8F705FF1C254144B67945" blockId="8.[151,1437,834,2013]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="0EC0EA92FFB8F705FF1C2541417F7E6D" box="[201,331,870,894]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">Coloration.</emphasis>
General color blackish brown (
<figureCitation id="A48F2A05FFB8F705FD172541434F7E6D" box="[706,891,870,894]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 64" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1865,1888]" captionTargetBox="[167,1425,208,1821]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1844]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 64. Adult of Macrocixius species. 53, 57, 61. M. giganteus. (53) Habitus, dorsal view; (57) Habitus, lateral view; (61) Face, ventral view. 54, 58, 62. M. grossus. (54) Habitus, dorsal view; (58) Habitus, lateral view; (62) Face, ventral view. 55, 59, 63. M. rarimaculatus. (55) Habitus, dorsal view; (59) Habitus, lateral view; (63) Face, ventral view. 56, 60, 64. M. unispinus. (56) Habitus, dorsal view; (60) Habitus, lateral view; (64) Face, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216904/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
Figs 
<number id="8A7C24A7FFB8F705FD2A254143787E6D" box="[767,844,870,894]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="56.6">56, 60</number>
, 
<number id="8A7C24A7FFB8F705FC8E2541434F7E6D" box="[859,891,870,894]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="64.0">64</number>
</figureCitation>
). Eyes yellowish brown alternating with black brown. Ocelli dull yellow. Face black brown, base and lateral margin deeply brown, areas around both ends of frontoclypeal suture with glassily yellow markings. Pronotum generally yellowish brown, area beside median carina and posterior margin of eyes black brown. Mesonotum black brown. Forewing colorless, hyaline, spreading with small dark brown markings on apical area, costal area and clavus area; stigma blackish brown; strip between bases of CuP and PCu black brown; yellow alternating with black brown on basal half of veins, apical half of veins mostly black brown. 
<collectingCountry id="44A37610FFB8F705FE562219418F7945" box="[387,443,1086,1110]" name="India" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">Hind</collectingCountry>
tarsi with platellae yellow. Abdomen blackish brown ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3C0B3680FFB8F705FF1C224442D2783C" blockId="8.[151,1437,834,2013]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="0EC0EA92FFB8F705FF1C224441327968" box="[201,262,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">Head</emphasis>
. Median ocellus (
<figureCitation id="A48F2A05FFB8F705FE1A224542127969" box="[463,550,1122,1146]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 52" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1416,204,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1884]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 52. Macrocixius unispinus sp. nov. (40) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (41) Face, ventral view; (42) Forewing; (43) Male genitalia, lateral view; (44) Pygofer and genital styles, ventral view; (45) Anal segment, dorsal view; (46) Anal segment, caudal view; (47) Right genital styles, ventral view; (48) Connective, dorsocephalad view; (49) Aedeagus, right side; (50) Aedeagus, left side; (51) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (52) Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216903/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
Figs 
<number id="8A7C24A7FFB8F705FDDD224542127969" box="[520,550,1122,1146]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="41.64">41</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="A48F2A05FFB8F705FDE6224542647969" box="[563,592,1122,1146]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 64" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1865,1888]" captionTargetBox="[167,1425,208,1821]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1844]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 64. Adult of Macrocixius species. 53, 57, 61. M. giganteus. (53) Habitus, dorsal view; (57) Habitus, lateral view; (61) Face, ventral view. 54, 58, 62. M. grossus. (54) Habitus, dorsal view; (58) Habitus, lateral view; (62) Face, ventral view. 55, 59, 63. M. rarimaculatus. (55) Habitus, dorsal view; (59) Habitus, lateral view; (63) Face, ventral view. 56, 60, 64. M. unispinus. (56) Habitus, dorsal view; (60) Habitus, lateral view; (64) Face, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216904/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">64</figureCitation>
) on the peak of frontoclypeal suture. Vertex (
<figureCitation id="A48F2A05FFB8F705FB9A224544937969" box="[1103,1191,1122,1146]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 52" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1416,204,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1884]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 52. Macrocixius unispinus sp. nov. (40) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (41) Face, ventral view; (42) Forewing; (43) Male genitalia, lateral view; (44) Pygofer and genital styles, ventral view; (45) Anal segment, dorsal view; (46) Anal segment, caudal view; (47) Right genital styles, ventral view; (48) Connective, dorsocephalad view; (49) Aedeagus, right side; (50) Aedeagus, left side; (51) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (52) Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216903/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
Figs 
<number id="8A7C24A7FFB8F705FB5D224544937969" box="[1160,1191,1122,1146]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="40.56">40</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="A48F2A05FFB8F705FB67224544FB7969" box="[1202,1231,1122,1146]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 64" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1865,1888]" captionTargetBox="[167,1425,208,1821]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1844]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 64. Adult of Macrocixius species. 53, 57, 61. M. giganteus. (53) Habitus, dorsal view; (57) Habitus, lateral view; (61) Face, ventral view. 54, 58, 62. M. grossus. (54) Habitus, dorsal view; (58) Habitus, lateral view; (62) Face, ventral view. 55, 59, 63. M. rarimaculatus. (55) Habitus, dorsal view; (59) Habitus, lateral view; (63) Face, ventral view. 56, 60, 64. M. unispinus. (56) Habitus, dorsal view; (60) Habitus, lateral view; (64) Face, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216904/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">56</figureCitation>
) 1.3 X wider than long; subapical carina joins lateral carinae at apical 
<number id="8A7C24A7FFB8F705FD2222A14336798D" box="[759,770,1158,1182]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="8A7C24A7FFB8F705FCD822A14329798D" box="[781,797,1158,1182]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="6.0">6</number>
; anterior margin slightly sinuous with middle archedly convex, posterior margin nearly trapezoidally concave; areolets before subapical carina concave, area behind subapical carina archedly concave; both two portions of median carina existing. Frons (
<figureCitation id="A48F2A05FFB8F705FBAC22E944E579F5" box="[1145,1233,1230,1254]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 52" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1416,204,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1884]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 52. Macrocixius unispinus sp. nov. (40) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (41) Face, ventral view; (42) Forewing; (43) Male genitalia, lateral view; (44) Pygofer and genital styles, ventral view; (45) Anal segment, dorsal view; (46) Anal segment, caudal view; (47) Right genital styles, ventral view; (48) Connective, dorsocephalad view; (49) Aedeagus, right side; (50) Aedeagus, left side; (51) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (52) Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216903/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
Figs 
<number id="8A7C24A7FFB8F705FB6622E944E579F5" box="[1203,1233,1230,1254]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="41.64">41</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="A48F2A05FFB8F705FB0A22E944C879F5" box="[1247,1276,1230,1254]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 64" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1865,1888]" captionTargetBox="[167,1425,208,1821]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1844]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 64. Adult of Macrocixius species. 53, 57, 61. M. giganteus. (53) Habitus, dorsal view; (57) Habitus, lateral view; (61) Face, ventral view. 54, 58, 62. M. grossus. (54) Habitus, dorsal view; (58) Habitus, lateral view; (62) Face, ventral view. 55, 59, 63. M. rarimaculatus. (55) Habitus, dorsal view; (59) Habitus, lateral view; (63) Face, ventral view. 56, 60, 64. M. unispinus. (56) Habitus, dorsal view; (60) Habitus, lateral view; (64) Face, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216904/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">64</figureCitation>
) 1.2 X longer than wide; anterior margin concave into an obtuse angle. Rostrum relatively long, reaching apex of hind femur, subapical segment 1.3 X longer than apical segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3C0B3680FFB8F705FF1C231B41A878F1" blockId="8.[151,1437,834,2013]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="0EC0EA92FFB8F705FF1C231B41CA7840" box="[201,510,1339,1363]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">Pronotum and mesonotum.</emphasis>
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="A48F2A05FFB8F705FD5C231D42D07841" box="[649,740,1338,1362]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 52" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1416,204,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1884]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 52. Macrocixius unispinus sp. nov. (40) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (41) Face, ventral view; (42) Forewing; (43) Male genitalia, lateral view; (44) Pygofer and genital styles, ventral view; (45) Anal segment, dorsal view; (46) Anal segment, caudal view; (47) Right genital styles, ventral view; (48) Connective, dorsocephalad view; (49) Aedeagus, right side; (50) Aedeagus, left side; (51) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (52) Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216903/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
Figs 
<number id="8A7C24A7FFB8F705FD10231D42D07841" box="[709,740,1338,1362]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="40.56">40</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="A48F2A05FFB8F705FD26231D43247841" box="[755,784,1338,1362]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 64" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1865,1888]" captionTargetBox="[167,1425,208,1821]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1844]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 64. Adult of Macrocixius species. 53, 57, 61. M. giganteus. (53) Habitus, dorsal view; (57) Habitus, lateral view; (61) Face, ventral view. 54, 58, 62. M. grossus. (54) Habitus, dorsal view; (58) Habitus, lateral view; (62) Face, ventral view. 55, 59, 63. M. rarimaculatus. (55) Habitus, dorsal view; (59) Habitus, lateral view; (63) Face, ventral view. 56, 60, 64. M. unispinus. (56) Habitus, dorsal view; (60) Habitus, lateral view; (64) Face, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216904/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">56</figureCitation>
) 1.3 X longer than vertex; intermediate carinae curving forward, vanishing near anterior margin of pronotum; both sides of median carina deeply concave; posterior margin concave, forming an obtuse angle. Mesonotum (
<figureCitation id="A48F2A05FFB8F705FCF923A543BD7889" box="[812,905,1410,1434]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 52" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1416,204,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1884]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 52. Macrocixius unispinus sp. nov. (40) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (41) Face, ventral view; (42) Forewing; (43) Male genitalia, lateral view; (44) Pygofer and genital styles, ventral view; (45) Anal segment, dorsal view; (46) Anal segment, caudal view; (47) Right genital styles, ventral view; (48) Connective, dorsocephalad view; (49) Aedeagus, right side; (50) Aedeagus, left side; (51) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (52) Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216903/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
Figs 
<number id="8A7C24A7FFB8F705FCBF23A543BD7889" box="[874,905,1410,1434]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="40.56">40</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="A48F2A05FFB8F705FC4C23A543827889" box="[921,950,1410,1434]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 64" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1865,1888]" captionTargetBox="[167,1425,208,1821]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1844]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 64. Adult of Macrocixius species. 53, 57, 61. M. giganteus. (53) Habitus, dorsal view; (57) Habitus, lateral view; (61) Face, ventral view. 54, 58, 62. M. grossus. (54) Habitus, dorsal view; (58) Habitus, lateral view; (62) Face, ventral view. 55, 59, 63. M. rarimaculatus. (55) Habitus, dorsal view; (59) Habitus, lateral view; (63) Face, ventral view. 56, 60, 64. M. unispinus. (56) Habitus, dorsal view; (60) Habitus, lateral view; (64) Face, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216904/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">56</figureCitation>
) 1.7 X longer than pronotum and vertex combined; lateral carinae slightly sinuous, inner sides of them with fine short striations, median carina vanishing on posteromedian area.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3C0B3680FFB8F705FF1C23D742157B39" blockId="8.[151,1437,834,2013]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="0EC0EA92FFB8F705FF1C23D741207B14" box="[201,276,1520,1543]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">Wings.</emphasis>
Forewing (
