<collectingCountry id="44A37610FFBBF706FE3027FB421C7CE7" box="[485,552,476,500]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="288">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry id="44A37610FFBBF706FDE327FB42B07CE7" box="[566,644,476,500]" name="Greece" pageId="11" pageNumber="288">Yunan</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="74AE650BFFBBF706FF1C242740D97FB4" pageId="11" pageNumber="288" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="3C0B3680FFBBF706FF1C242740D97FB4" blockId="11.[151,1437,151,716]" pageId="11" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis id="0EC0EA92FFBBF706FF1C242741097F0B" bold="true" box="[201,317,512,536]" pageId="11" pageNumber="288">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="FBB44D03FFBBF706FD47242643177F0B" box="[658,803,513,536]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Macrocixius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giganteus">
<emphasis id="0EC0EA92FFBBF706FD47242643177F0B" box="[658,803,513,536]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="288">M. giganteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the main differences are as follows: (
<number id="8A7C24A7FFBBF706FB1827D844ED7F04" box="[1229,1241,511,535]" pageId="11" pageNumber="288" value="1.0">1</number>
) forewing of this new species with fewer dark markings; (
<number id="8A7C24A7FFBBF706FDB52403425B7F2F" box="[608,623,548,572]" pageId="11" pageNumber="288" value="2.0">2</number>
) the spines on the left side of the aedeagus differ from the latter in size, direction and position; (
<number id="8A7C24A7FFBBF706FE72246041817F4C" box="[423,437,583,607]" pageId="11" pageNumber="288" value="3.0">3</number>
) the longest spine on right side of aedeagus about 
<date id="480A1040FFBBF706FC2E246044117F73" box="[1019,1061,583,608]" pageId="11" pageNumber="288">
<number id="8A7C24A7FFBBF706FC2E2460443D7F4C" box="[1019,1033,583,607]" pageId="11" pageNumber="288" value="2.0">2</number>
X
</date>
longer than the shortest one, not crossing dorsal margin of aedeagus to left; (
<number id="8A7C24A7FFBBF706FD40244B42907F97" box="[661,676,620,644]" pageId="11" pageNumber="288" value="4.0">4</number>
) flagellum of this new species with one short spine on the dorsal margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="74AE650BFFBBF706FF1C249345A07FDF" box="[201,1428,692,716]" pageId="11" pageNumber="288" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="3C0B3680FFBBF706FF1C249345A07FDF" blockId="11.[151,1437,151,716]" box="[201,1428,692,716]" pageId="11" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis id="0EC0EA92FFBBF706FF1C2493417B7FDF" bold="true" box="[201,335,692,716]" pageId="11" pageNumber="288">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is derived from the Latin words “ 
<taxonomicName id="FBB44D03FFBBF706FC972492439A7FDF" box="[834,942,693,716]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Macrocixius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unispinus">
<emphasis id="0EC0EA92FFBBF706FC972492439A7FDF" box="[834,942,693,716]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="288">unispinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, which refers to flagellum with one spine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
